The power factor is the ratio of the actual power consumed by a load to the apparent power measured by a standard power meter. A low power factor means that the actual power consumption is much higher than the apparent power, which can result in inefficient use of electricity and excessive heating of the electrical system. PFC is used to increase the efficiency of electrical systems by reducing the power factor of loads that have a low power factor. There are several methods of PFC, including passive and active techniques.
